.\" Manpage for bitcoin-tax(1) — tax-label vocabulary (FEAT-038).
.TH BITCOIN-TAX 1 "2026-05-21" "bitcoin 1.23.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin\-tax \- tax-label vocabulary and (in 1.25.0) reporting

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin tax label
.I wallet
.I outpoint
.B --as
.I category
.RI [ "--note text" ]
.br
.B bitcoin tax help

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin tax
is the tax-workflow entry point. In 1.23.0 it ships exactly one
subcommand \(em
.B label
\(em which is a discoverable shorthand for
.BR "bitcoin wallet label" .
The report engine
.RB ( "tax report-de" )
and the BTC/EUR price oracle
.RB ( "tax price" )
land in 1.25.0 with FEAT-039 / FEAT-040.

The
.B label
verb persists a category from the closed FEAT-038 taxonomy
against a wallet outpoint (UTXO, transaction, or address). The
13 valid categories are
.BR self-transfer ,
.BR income ,
.BR gift-in ,
.BR gift-out ,
.BR purchase ,
.BR sale ,
.BR spend ,
.BR fee ,
.BR lending-out ,
.BR lending-in ,
.BR loss-claim ,
.BR channel-open ,
.BR channel-close .

For free-form annotations (counterparty names, invoice IDs)
that aren't part of the tax taxonomy, use
.BR "bitcoin wallet label <wallet> <outpoint> --free-text <text>"
instead.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "--as " "category"
The tax category to tag the outpoint with. Must be one of the
13 categories listed above.
.TP
.BI "--note " "text"
Optional free-text annotation stored alongside the tax category
(e.g.
.IR "kraken Q1 2025" ).

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.BI "label " "wallet outpoint" " --as " category " [--note " text "]"
Persist a tax category on the outpoint. Byte-identical to
.BR "bitcoin wallet label <wallet> <outpoint> --tax <category>"
\(em the
.B tax
prefix exists purely for discoverability of the tax workflow.
.TP
.B help
List the closed taxonomy and the planned 1.25.0 verbs.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
Missing required argument, or unknown subcommand.
.TP
.B 6
Category not in the closed taxonomy (error names the valid set).
.TP
.B \(>=1
Other errors propagate from
.B wallet label
unchanged.

.SH FILES
.TP
.IB <wallet-repo>/labels/utxo
TSV store for per-UTXO labels. With FEAT-038, rows tagged via
.B --as
have three columns:
.IB outpoint TAB category TAB note .
Legacy two-column rows (free-text only) remain valid and read
correctly.
.TP
.IB <wallet-repo>/labels/tx
TSV store for per-transaction labels, same format.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Inherited from
.BR bitcoin-wallet (1).
The wallet's
.B labels/
directory lives under
.IB $XDG_DATA_HOME /bitcoin/wallets/ <name> /labels/ .

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR bitcoin-wallet (1)

.SH HISTORY
Verb introduced in bitcoin 1.23.0 (FEAT-038). The 13-category
taxonomy lands in this release; the report engine
.RB ( "tax report-de" )
and the BTC/EUR price oracle
.RB ( "tax price" )
follow in 1.25.0 (FEAT-039 + FEAT-040). The taxonomy is
expected to remain stable across those releases.
